when she told me...

702
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:52,243
to enjoy the food.

703
00:43:52,243 --> 00:43:53,573
(Neuroscientific Investigation Team)

704
00:43:53,573 --> 00:43:55,533
I almost burst into tears.

705
00:43:56,183 --> 00:43:59,073
Only Cherri speaks to me
with that much warmth.

706
00:43:59,683 --> 00:44:01,453
In Japan,

707
00:44:01,453 --> 00:44:04,854
there are men who marry
virtual people like her.

708
00:44:04,854 --> 00:44:06,044
Is that so?

709
00:44:06,694 --> 00:44:09,664
Why don't I start obsessing
over Cherri, then?

710
00:44:09,664 --> 00:44:10,823
I urge you to hold back,

711
00:44:10,823 --> 00:44:12,964
or your wife might bash your head in.

712
00:44:12,964 --> 00:44:14,154
Shall we?

713
00:44:20,674 --> 00:44:21,864
Hold on.

714
00:44:22,774 --> 00:44:26,634
What were you two secretly discussing?

715
00:44:27,343 --> 00:44:30,404
Something that you will
greatly appreciate.

716
00:44:31,484 --> 00:44:33,613
Dr. Shin, the consultant for...

717
00:44:33,613 --> 00:44:35,504
the Neuroscientific Investigation Team.

718
00:44:35,683 --> 00:44:36,683
We set up a press conference...

719
00:44:36,683 --> 00:44:39,124
at which you will speak
on behalf of the team.

720
00:44:39,124 --> 00:44:40,544
- I refuse.
- Sorry?

721
00:44:41,354 --> 00:44:42,683
But why?

722
00:44:43,024 --> 00:44:44,823
You love to seem superior.

723
00:44:44,823 --> 00:44:46,354
How many times must I tell you...

724
00:44:46,633 --> 00:44:48,683
that I don't seem superior? I just am.

725
00:44:49,433 --> 00:44:51,004
And like I said,

726
00:44:51,004 --> 00:44:53,464
now that the case has been wrapped up,

727
00:44:53,703 --> 00:44:55,024
I will get going.

728
00:44:58,774 --> 00:45:00,763
But...

729
00:45:04,714 --> 00:45:06,814
Don't just stand there
and get him to stay.

730
00:45:06,814 --> 00:45:09,774
Why is it always me
who has to beg and be clingy?

731
00:45:11,323 --> 00:45:12,614
Dr. Brain!

732
00:45:13,794 --> 00:45:16,013
Dr. Brain, come on.

733
00:45:16,194 --> 00:45:18,093
If there's anything you need,
just tell me.

734
00:45:18,093 --> 00:45:20,093
I'll pay for it out of my own pocket.

735
00:45:20,093 --> 00:45:22,154
(Keep Quiet)

736
00:45:22,433 --> 00:45:23,694
There is something I want.

737
00:45:24,164 --> 00:45:25,703
What is it? Just tell me.

738
00:45:25,703 --> 00:45:28,663
I'll take out a loan in dollars
to get you what you want.

739
00:45:28,734 --> 00:45:30,564
I want you to leave.

740
00:45:31,703 --> 00:45:34,174
Hold on. Let me say this again.

741
00:45:34,174 --> 00:45:36,174
This is my place of work.

742
00:45:36,743 --> 00:45:39,873
If anyone should leave, it should be you.

743
00:45:40,183 --> 00:45:42,203
It's why I'm leaving. So what's the issue?

744
00:45:42,653 --> 00:45:43,973
You're a weird one.

745
00:45:45,453 --> 00:45:47,044
But that's not what I meant.

746
00:45:47,053 --> 00:45:48,544
Are you really leaving us?

747
00:45:48,794 --> 00:45:50,363
But we grew close while working together.

748
00:45:50,363 --> 00:45:51,524
How about a drink?

749
00:45:51,524 --> 00:45:53,064
If not, how about a meal?

750
00:45:53,064 --> 00:45:54,453
Beef. It'll be on me.

751
00:45:56,763 --> 00:45:59,194
He's just leaving
without even considering my offer.

752
00:45:59,674 --> 00:46:00,773
He's going to turn around.

753
00:46:00,774 --> 00:46:02,064
He's going to turn around.

754
00:46:02,133 --> 00:46:03,464
Turn around.

755
00:46:03,573 --> 00:46:05,364
Turn around.

756
00:46:07,914 --> 00:46:09,104
(Keep Quiet)

757
00:46:10,243 --> 00:46:13,004
I can't believe he didn't
glance back in my direction.

758
00:46:16,653 --> 00:46:18,944
Could I have grown attached to him?

759
00:46:19,354 --> 00:46:20,984
Why am I sad to see him leave?

760
00:46:25,064 --> 00:46:26,254
Your last case?

761
00:46:28,093 --> 00:46:29,283
But why?

762
00:46:30,263 --> 00:46:31,263
Why not consult on more cases?

763
00:46:31,263 --> 00:46:32,433
You're the one who said it was weird.

764
00:46:32,433 --> 00:46:34,403
That was because you preached revenge,

765
00:46:34,403 --> 00:46:36,864
which wasn't like you at all.

766
00:46:37,144 --> 00:46:39,774
You seemed to be immersed
in solving cases these days,

767
00:46:39,774 --> 00:46:40,964
so why did you quit?

768
00:46:41,774 --> 00:46:43,104
I guess you're right.

769
00:46:43,343 --> 00:46:45,543
I wouldn't have come across
someone with Capgras syndrome...

770
00:46:45,544 --> 00:46:47,803
had I been cooped up
at the research center.

771
00:46:48,754 --> 00:46:51,044
That reminds me. How did the case unravel?

772
00:46:52,484 --> 00:46:54,084
The wife was the killer.

773
00:46:55,493 --> 00:46:57,194
Her husband Heo Bum Soo,
who was the patient,

774
00:46:57,194 --> 00:46:59,023
took the fall for his wife.

775
00:46:59,024 --> 00:47:00,384
I see.

776
00:47:02,064 --> 00:47:05,223
Mr. Heo must love his wife dearly.

777
00:47:07,303 --> 00:47:08,794
Not you too.

778
00:47:10,674 --> 00:47:13,033
Why is everyone going on about love?

779
00:47:13,274 --> 00:47:14,763
Love...

780
00:47:14,914 --> 00:47:18,112
is only an electric signal
exchanged between neurons.

781
00:47:18,113 --> 00:47:20,414
People let those signals take over
and fall head over heels for others.

782
00:47:20,414 --> 00:47:23,573
Then comes betrayal,
hatred, and suffering.

783
00:47:23,653 --> 00:47:25,973
But after all that, they repeat
the journey with someone new.

784
00:47:27,924 --> 00:47:29,183
How pathetic is that?

785
00:47:30,194 --> 00:47:31,384
Ha Ru.

786
00:47:33,194 --> 00:47:36,254
Do you know when those electric signals...

787
00:47:37,104 --> 00:47:38,354
shine the brightest?

788
00:47:40,004 --> 00:47:42,093
You're asking that with an answer in mind.

789
00:47:42,174 --> 00:47:45,334
Exactly. It's when people are in love.

790
00:47:46,674 --> 00:47:50,734
Like you said, loving someone
ends painfully in a lot of cases.

791
00:47:50,783 --> 00:47:51,973
However,

792
00:47:52,444 --> 00:47:54,414
the brain will forever remember...

793
00:47:54,414 --> 00:47:56,573
how our neurons twinkled for someone else.

794
00:47:57,323 --> 00:47:58,513
And I believe...

795
00:47:59,223 --> 00:48:02,114
that those memories keep us going in life.

796
00:48:06,294 --> 00:48:07,484
Ha Ru,

797
00:48:08,294 --> 00:48:10,524
there's only one thing I wish for you.

798
00:48:15,433 --> 00:48:18,493
I want you to feel that blissful moment...

799
00:48:21,044 --> 00:48:22,533
once in your life.

800
00:48:25,644 --> 00:48:28,174
It's love.

801
00:48:29,314 --> 00:48:32,913
Love has you in pain.

802
00:48:34,953 --> 00:48:36,654
How did you know that?

803
00:48:36,964 --> 00:48:39,013
There's no need to be surprised.

804
00:48:39,894 --> 00:48:43,524
It only took minor observation skills.

805
00:48:44,903 --> 00:48:47,964
You're no longer wearing your ring.

806
00:48:50,944 --> 00:48:54,663
My superiors ordered me
not to speak to you.

807
00:48:54,874 --> 00:48:56,774
Was it your girlfriend or your wife?

808
00:49:00,783 --> 00:49:02,343
My girlfriend.

809
00:49:02,723 --> 00:49:03,913
Then it's all good.

810
00:49:05,254 --> 00:49:07,952
You'd be in trouble if it was your wife.

811
00:49:07,953 --> 00:49:11,413
Because you'd have to lose something
that belongs to you.

812
00:49:12,093 --> 00:49:15,323
You might have to fight the urge
to beat her up.

813
00:49:16,064 --> 00:49:17,323
However,

814
00:49:18,263 --> 00:49:20,694
girlfriends are expendable.

815
00:49:23,473 --> 00:49:25,093
Love...

816
00:49:26,414 --> 00:49:29,513
is like a program
utilized by our brains...

817
00:49:29,513 --> 00:49:33,143
that was designed to help pass on our DNA.

818
00:49:33,953 --> 00:49:36,714
Another expendable girlfriend
will appear...

819
00:49:37,183 --> 00:49:39,544
who'll serve as a medium for you.

820
00:49:39,894 --> 00:49:43,183
So don't be too heartbroken.

821
00:49:46,694 --> 00:49:47,884
Sure.

822
00:49:50,033 --> 00:49:52,024
Those foolish...

823
00:49:52,604 --> 00:49:55,174
make a huge fuss as though love...

824
00:49:55,174 --> 00:49:57,933
is the world's most beautiful concept.

825
00:49:58,073 --> 00:49:59,334
But that isn't the case.

826
00:49:59,944 --> 00:50:02,343
Love is the root of all evil.

827
00:50:02,343 --> 00:50:03,904
Just think about it.

828
00:50:04,183 --> 00:50:08,004
Think of all the crimes
that are committed out of love.

829
00:50:10,984 --> 00:50:14,913
The love for a deity
leads to religious wars.

830
00:50:16,624 --> 00:50:20,123
Parental love leads to suicide...

831
00:50:21,694 --> 00:50:24,123
after murdering their innocent child.

832
00:50:25,703 --> 00:50:27,174
Some manically murder
their ex-boyfriend or ex-girlfriend...

833
00:50:27,174 --> 00:50:29,294
because they can't get over them.

834
00:50:30,104 --> 00:50:32,393
You hear of that often on the news.

835
00:50:33,274 --> 00:50:34,464
They killed...

836
00:50:34,973 --> 00:50:38,033
because they were deeply in love.

837
00:50:39,714 --> 00:50:41,854
Whether it was driven
by possessiveness or jealousy,

838
00:50:41,854 --> 00:50:44,143
love was at the heart of it.

839
00:50:47,653 --> 00:50:51,154
I also knew someone who was like that.

840
00:50:52,424 --> 00:50:53,924
Someone who killed...

841
00:50:54,894 --> 00:50:56,593
in the name of love.

842
00:51:07,374 --> 00:51:08,964
I want to forget,

843
00:51:13,354 --> 00:51:14,674
but I can't.

844
00:51:22,354 --> 00:51:24,453
The memories have been
creeping up on me lately.

845
00:51:35,774 --> 00:51:36,964
I'm sorry.

846
00:51:40,914 --> 00:51:42,104
I'm sorry.

847
00:51:54,053 --> 00:51:56,183
Yi Na. Daughter?

848
00:51:57,093 --> 00:51:58,714
Yi Na?

849
00:52:02,593 --> 00:52:03,794
My daughter,

850
00:52:04,064 --> 00:52:05,334
you'll be late at this rate.

851
00:52:05,334 --> 00:52:08,524
Seriously? I messed it up because of you.

852
00:52:08,874 --> 00:52:10,644
- Where?
- Right here.

853
00:52:10,644 --> 00:52:12,403
My eyebrows don't match!

854
00:52:12,403 --> 00:52:13,743
You ruined them.

855
00:52:13,743 --> 00:52:15,444
Nothing's ruined. They're the same.

856
00:52:15,444 --> 00:52:18,033
They look exactly the same,
so come and eat.

857
00:52:18,914 --> 00:52:20,683
- I'm late.
- You said you'd eat.

858
00:52:20,683 --> 00:52:22,253
I said I was late. Bye.

859
00:52:22,254 --> 00:52:24,484
If you skip classes,
I'll dock your allowance!

860
00:52:24,484 --> 00:52:26,913
Yes, of course. See you.

861
00:52:30,924 --> 00:52:32,413
She said goodbye, though.

862
00:52:41,004 --> 00:52:42,364
She said she'd eat.

863
00:52:45,473 --> 00:52:47,404
She said she'd eat.

864
00:52:49,714 --> 00:52:51,803
It's too much work.

865
00:52:52,144 --> 00:52:54,643
It's harder than catching killers.

866
00:52:57,953 --> 00:52:59,174
Jeez...

867
00:53:17,944 --> 00:53:19,564
Dr. Brain.

868
00:53:20,473 --> 00:53:22,004
I wonder if he eats at all.

869
00:53:22,374 --> 00:53:24,433
He's such a jerk.

870
00:53:25,314 --> 00:53:27,774
He never called once since he quit.

871
00:53:28,084 --> 00:53:29,303
No.

872
00:53:29,354 --> 00:53:32,873
It's stupid of me
to even expect him to call.

873
00:53:35,194 --> 00:53:36,444
Shall I call him?

874
00:53:41,694 --> 00:53:44,854
No. Why bother a busy man?

875
00:53:46,374 --> 00:53:47,623
No.

876
00:53:48,803 --> 00:53:51,464
Won't he like it if I ask how he's doing?

877
00:53:52,544 --> 00:53:53,734
Yes.

878
00:54:02,683 --> 00:54:03,952
Hello, Captain Seul.

879
00:54:03,953 --> 00:54:05,843
Come on out. I'm outside.

880
00:54:13,763 --> 00:54:15,024
In hiking attire?

881
00:54:15,933 --> 00:54:18,303
Yes. If you don't have any,
come out as is.

882
00:54:18,303 --> 00:54:20,424
I'll buy you a whole new outfit.

883
00:54:20,473 --> 00:54:22,694
No, I have hiking clothes.

884
00:54:22,803 --> 00:54:25,802
Why do you suddenly want to go hiking?

885
00:54:25,803 --> 00:54:27,864
You have five minutes. Be quick.

886
00:54:29,914 --> 00:54:31,933
Hello? Captain Seul?

887
00:54:34,453 --> 00:54:35,703
What was that about?

888
00:54:36,314 --> 00:54:37,913
Why are we going hiking?

889
00:54:39,323 --> 00:54:41,444
Five minutes? Shoot.

890
00:54:46,093 --> 00:54:47,323
Darn it.

891
00:54:49,363 --> 00:54:51,424
Oh, no. Mister!

892
00:54:57,843 --> 00:54:59,334
Wait for me.

893
00:54:59,374 --> 00:55:00,564
Mister!

894
00:55:01,343 --> 00:55:02,533
Wait.

895
00:55:04,743 --> 00:55:05,933
Mister!

896
00:55:07,613 --> 00:55:08,843
Darn it.

897
00:55:09,113 --> 00:55:11,714
I'll get penalty points if I'm late today.

898
00:55:13,124 --> 00:55:15,913
I can't breathe. I shouldn't have run.

899
00:55:28,573 --> 00:55:29,823
Geum Yi Na.

900
00:55:33,444 --> 00:55:35,134
Why are you grinning when we're late?

901
00:55:35,374 --> 00:55:38,803
Thanks to being late,
I get to ride the best kind of bus.

902
00:55:39,783 --> 00:55:41,274
The bus you're on.

903
00:55:42,453 --> 00:55:44,714
What kind of pick-up line is that?

904
00:55:45,183 --> 00:55:46,884
It's corny, and I hate it.

905
00:55:47,153 --> 00:55:49,444
- What do you do after school?
- I have extra classes.

906
00:55:51,194 --> 00:55:52,683
Shall we watch a movie instead?

907
00:55:52,723 --> 00:55:54,754
The model student would do that?

908
00:55:54,894 --> 00:55:56,223
Yes or no?

909
00:55:57,664 --> 00:55:59,053
I can't go.

910
00:55:59,504 --> 00:56:02,194
My dad said he'd call to check on me.

911
00:56:03,803 --> 00:56:05,373
What will you watch?

912
00:56:05,374 --> 00:56:07,864
- Anything's fine.
- I can't be bothered.

913
00:56:08,573 --> 00:56:09,933
Hey.

914
00:56:11,544 --> 00:56:12,734
Guys.

915
00:56:16,783 --> 00:56:18,143
Look at her grin.

916
00:56:18,524 --> 00:56:20,214
Who's the loser next to her?

917
00:56:26,964 --> 00:56:29,154
Oh, my gosh.

918
00:56:29,763 --> 00:56:31,254
Why do you suddenly...

919
00:56:31,803 --> 00:56:34,493
want me to watch my health?

920
00:56:34,973 --> 00:56:38,064
Why do you suddenly want to start hiking?

921
00:56:38,803 --> 00:56:40,464
Look at the view!

922
00:56:41,444 --> 00:56:44,134
I have a plan.

923
00:56:45,013 --> 00:56:46,234
What?

924
00:56:48,153 --> 00:56:50,274
What's the secret to...

925
00:56:50,783 --> 00:56:52,044
a successful confession?

926
00:56:53,024 --> 00:56:55,593
Your chances improve if you confess
somewhere high and dangerous...

927
00:56:55,593 --> 00:56:57,154
when out of breath.

928
00:56:57,164 --> 00:56:59,854
High up, dangerous, out of breath.

929
00:57:00,564 --> 00:57:02,484
All things that increase your heartbeat.

930
00:57:03,834 --> 00:57:05,053
That's right.

931
00:57:05,604 --> 00:57:07,194
Our brain...

932
00:57:07,533 --> 00:57:09,593
constantly monitors our body.

933
00:57:09,674 --> 00:57:12,834
If our heart races,
it tries to identify the cause.

934
00:57:13,104 --> 00:57:14,343
If you were to confess then,

935
00:57:14,343 --> 00:57:18,404
he'd think, "My heart's racing
because I like her."

936
00:57:21,814 --> 00:57:24,544
I have something to say.

937
00:57:24,723 --> 00:57:27,584
You have something to say? Go ahead.

938
00:57:27,624 --> 00:57:29,814
